================================================================================
  GBH_results — Five-Dimensional Collective Hamiltonian (5DCH/GBH) Results
================================================================================

This folder contains the results of the General Bohr Hamiltonian (GBH, i.e.
five-dimensional collective Hamiltonian, 5DCH) calculations for even-even
nuclei, based on the triaxial RHB + PC-PK1 potential energy surfaces.


1. FOLDER STRUCTURE
================================================================================

GBH_results/
|
|-- {El}_iso/                      # Isotopic chain directory (e.g. Ar_iso, Ca_iso)
|   |
|   |-- {El}{A}/                   # Per-nuclide directory (e.g. Ar36, Ca40)
|   |   |-- GBH.dat               # Input parameter file for the GBH code
|   |   |-- run                    # Compiled GBH executable (ELF binary)
|   |   |-- GBH.out               # Main output: energy levels, transitions, moments
|   |   |-- cpar.out              # Collective parameters on the (beta, gamma) mesh
|   |   |-- wave.out              # Collective wave functions |F_K|^2 on (beta, gamma)
|   |   |-- nohup.out             # Runtime log (Hamiltonian matrix dimensions per I)
|   |   |-- {A}{El}_01+.png       # Wave function density plot for 0_1^+ state
|   |   |-- {A}{El}_02+.png       # Wave function density plot for 0_2^+ state
|   |   |-- {A}{El}_03+.png       # Wave function density plot for 0_3^+ state
|   |   |-- {A}{El}_04+.png       # Wave function density plot for 0_4^+ state
|   |
|   |-- Energy_{El}.out           # Excitation energies summary for the chain
|   |-- BE2_{El}.out              # B(E2) values: B(2n+ -> 0n+) for n=1..4
|   |-- BE2_2_{El}.out            # Additional B(E2) values (in-band transitions)
|   |-- Deform_{El}.out           # Effective deformation parameters (beta, cos3gamma)
|   |-- Quad_{El}.out             # Quadrupole shape invariants <q^2>, <q^3>
|   |-- rho2_{El}.out             # E0 transition strengths rho^2(E0)


2. GBH.dat — INPUT PARAMETER FILE
================================================================================

Controls the GBH diagonalization for a single nucleus. Key parameters:

  nucleus    : element name, proton number Z, neutron number N
  spin       : Imin, Imax — range of angular momenta to solve
  para \mu   : imu (0=fit, 1=fixed), remu — cranking mass scaling
  levels     : number of eigenstates per spin to output
  observ     : observable level (0=none, 1=E0, 2=E0+E2, 3=E0+E2+M1)
  wave fun   : 1 = output wave functions, 0 = skip
  nbeta, ngam, npar : mesh dimensions in beta, gamma, and number of
                       collective parameters (potential V, mass B_k, ...)


3. GBH.out — MAIN OUTPUT (DETAILED DESCRIPTION)
================================================================================

The primary output file for each nucleus. Contains three major sections:

--- 3.1  READER BLOCK ---

  Echoes the input parameters (nucleus, spin range, mesh sizes, etc.).

--- 3.2  LEVELS BLOCK ---

  E_0 : absolute ground-state energy (MeV), i.e. the minimum of the
        collective potential mapped from constrained RHB.

  For each angular momentum I = Imin .. Imax:
    ntot : dimension of the GBH Hamiltonian matrix for this I
    Columns: I, n (state index), E_x (excitation energy in MeV)
    States are listed from n=1 (yrast) to n=nlevel.

  Example:
    I=  2   ntot= 234
     2   1    3.478746       ← 2_1^+ excitation energy
     2   2    7.233773       ← 2_2^+ excitation energy
     ...

--- 3.3  TRANSITION BLOCK ---

  (a) Monopole moment (E0 diagonal matrix elements):

    For each state (I, n):
      <In|E0|In>    : diagonal E0 matrix element
      ave beta      : expectation value of quadrupole deformation beta
      del<b>        : fluctuation (width) of beta
      ave gamma     : expectation value of triaxial angle gamma (degrees)
      del<g>        : fluctuation (width) of gamma
      K=0, K=2, K=4 : K-component decomposition of the wave function (%)

  (b) rho^2(E0) — Monopole transition strengths:

    For each pair (I, n1) and (I, n2):
      <In1|E0|In2>  : off-diagonal E0 matrix element
      rho^2(E0)     : monopole transition strength (dimensionless, x10^3)

  (c) E2 transition — Electric quadrupole transitions:

    For each pair (I1, n1) <-> (I2, n2):
      <f||E2||i>      : reduced E2 matrix element (eb)
      B(E2, I1->I2)   : reduced transition probability (e^2 b^2)
      B(E2, I2->I1)   : reverse direction (e^2 b^2)
      WU columns       : same values in Weisskopf units (W.u.)

    For I1 = I2 (diagonal), the E2 matrix element gives the
    spectroscopic quadrupole moment Q_s (eb).

  (d) Quadrupole shape invariants (at the end):

    quadr2 : <q^2> for states 0_1^+, 0_2^+, 0_3^+, 0_4^+
    quadr3 : <q^3> for the same states
    beteff : effective deformation beta_eff derived from <q^2>
    cos3ga : cos(3*gamma_eff) derived from <q^2> and <q^3>


4. OTHER PER-NUCLIDE FILES
================================================================================

  cpar.out   : Collective parameters tabulated on the (beta, gamma) mesh.
               Columns: beta, gamma(deg), E_pot(MeV), B_1, B_2, B_3, ...
               (mass parameters, moments of inertia, zero-point energies)

  wave.out   : Collective wave function densities |F_K(beta,gamma)|^2
               for each state (I, n), tabulated on the (beta, gamma) mesh.
               Used to generate the density plots {A}{El}_0n+.png.

  nohup.out  : Runtime log showing Hamiltonian matrix dimension (Dim)
               for each angular momentum I.

  {A}{El}_0n+.png : Plots of the collective wave function probability
               density in the (beta, gamma) plane for the first four
               0^+ states (n=1,2,3,4).


5. ISOTOPIC CHAIN SUMMARY FILES
================================================================================

Located in each {El}_iso/ directory, these collect key observables across
all isotopes in the chain:

  Energy_{El}.out  : Excitation energies (MeV) —
                     E(2_1^+), E(4_1^+), E(0_2^+), E(2_2^+),
                     E(0_3^+), E(2_3^+), E(0_4^+), E(2_4^+)

  BE2_{El}.out     : B(E2; 2_n^+ -> 0_n^+) in e^2 b^2 for n=1..4

  BE2_2_{El}.out   : Additional B(E2) values (e.g. in-band transitions)

  Deform_{El}.out  : Effective deformation parameters —
                     beta_eff and cos(3*gamma_eff) for 0_1^+ .. 0_4^+

  Quad_{El}.out    : Quadrupole shape invariants —
                     <q^2> and <q^3> for 0_1^+ .. 0_4^+

  rho2_{El}.out    : E0 transition strengths rho^2(E0) —
                     rho^2(0_2^+ -> 0_1^+), rho^2(0_3^+ -> 0_1^+), etc.


6. REFERENCES
================================================================================

[1] Y. L. Yang, Y. K. Wang, P. W. Zhao, and Z. P. Li,
    Phys. Rev. C 104, 054312 (2021)
[2] Y. L. Yang, P. W. Zhao, and Z. P. Li,
    Phys. Rev. C 107, 024308 (2023)
